The State House of Assembly Special Screening Committee deployed to Zamfara by the All Progressives Congress National Secretariat has completed its assignment in the state. The seven-member committee which was chaired by Hon. Babagana Tijjani Banki arrived in the state and commenced the exercise at the Command Guest House, Gusau. A total number 28 aspirants vying for the stateâ€™s legislative seat in the 2023 general elections were screened. The chairman who commended the conduct of the aspirants in the exercise explained that his committee gave equal opportunity to all of them to appear and be screened. Banki added that the report of the committee would be submitted to the APC National Secretariat, Abuja. He said the APC would remain committed to justice, fair play and work in decorum to enhance full participation of members and examplary internal democracy. Other members of the committee included Hon. Wakil Aliyu, Abubakar Yarima, Faruk Ibrahim Tsiga, Hon. Abdullahi Musa and Adamu Ibrahim, while Fadima Ibrahim is the secretary. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com